## Advanced Editing

### Imports, Signatures, Decorators

```sh
echo 'use std::collections::HashMap;' >>file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/imports.{{ ext }}
echo 'fn process(input: &str, opts: Options) -> Result<()>' \
    >file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/process@/signature.{{ ext }}
echo '#[instrument]' >>file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/process@/decorators.{{ ext }}
```

### Delete a Symbol or Line Range

```sh
rmdir file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/old_helper@/    # splices out from source
rm file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/old_helper.{{ ext }}  # shorthand — same effect
rm file.{{ ext }}@/lines:10-20                # delete a line range
```

---

## Advanced Batch Editing

### Append as Last Child (impl blocks, modules)

```sh
echo 'fn method() { ... }' >file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/MyImpl@/edit/append
```

### Review Before Applying

```sh
ls file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/edit/staged/               # list staged actions
cat file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/edit/staged/10-replace.diff  # preview one
rm file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/Foo@/edit/staged/10-replace.diff   # remove one without applying
cat @/edit/staged.diff                                       # global preview (all files)
```

Cross-file batch edits: stage in multiple files, apply with `rm @/edit/staged.diff`.

