## Anti-Patterns

| Anti-pattern | Correct approach |
|-|-|
| `Read file.{{ ext }}` (raw file read) | `Read file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/OVERVIEW.md` then targeted symbol |
| `Grep "fn process" src/` | `ls file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/by-kind/fn/` or `OVERVIEW.md` |
| `Grep "process" src/` for callers | `Read file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/process@/CALLERS.md` |
| Full file read for imports | `Read file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/imports.{{ ext }}` |
| Editing raw source files | Edit `@/symbols/` bodies (tree-sitter validated) |
| Grep + manual line math for symbol | `readlink file.{{ ext }}@/symbols/at-line/42` (instant) |
| Reading N files for call sites | `CALLERS.md` has inline code context for all sites |
| Modifying without checking callers | **Always** read `CALLERS.md` first |
| Using symbol paths after a write without re-reading | Re-read `OVERVIEW.md` after writes — the symbol table may have changed |
| `Bash(cat file@/OVERVIEW.md)` for single reads | Use the **Read tool** — it's the default for all single-path `@/` reads |
| Guessing path variations on `ENOENT` | `ls symbols/` or `OVERVIEW.md` to find the current name |
| Sequential direct writes to 2+ symbols | Batch edit staging — atomic, validated |

